    {
      "title": "How to See Query Text",
      "type": "text",
      "gridPos": { "h": 6, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 24 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## How to see actual DB/Redis query text\n\n1. Click any **Trace ID** in the tables above → opens in Explore\n2. In Explore, click on a span to expand it\n3. Look for these fields:\n   - `span_attr:db.statement` — PostgreSQL/ClickHouse SQL query\n   - `span_attr:db.statement` — Redis command (GET, SET, etc.)\n   - `span_attr:db.query.text` — alternative query field\n   - `span_attr:db.sql.table` — table name\n   - `span_attr:db.rows_affected` — rows affected\n\n### Useful filters in Explore\n- PostgreSQL only: `\"span_attr:db.system\":postgresql`\n- Redis only: `\"span_attr:db.system\":redis`\n- ClickHouse only: `\"span_attr:db.system\":clickhouse`\n- Sort by duration: `| sort by (duration) desc`"
      }
    }
